[CALCITE-1990]Make RelDistribution to extends RelMultipleTrait
body:
Make RelDistribution extends RelMultipleTrait. It will be used for satisfying between traits.
` select T1.c1,count(*) from T1 join T2 on T1.c1=T2.d1 group by T1.c1;`
`select T2.d1,count(*) from T1 join T2 on T1.c1=T2.d1 group by T1.d1;`

Supposed Plan:

     SortedAggregate(group by T1.c1 or group by T2.d1)
        SortedMergeJoin
             SortExchange(c1)
                T1(c1)
            SortExchange(d1)
                T2(d1)

For two query, if the Distribution trait of SortedMergeJoin is RelCompositeTrait with distribution hash(c1) and distribution hash(d1), then the distribution of SortedMergeJoin satisfy SortedAggregate. there is no SortExchange between SortedAggregate and SortedMergeJoin.

[CALCITE-1787] - Add ThetaSketch and HyperUnique support to Calcite via Rolled up columns
body:
## Rolled Up Columns
This PR adds logic in Calcite to handle 'Rolled Up' columns - columns that have their data rolled up in some manner. This means adding additional validation logic into SqlValidatorImpl. The extra logic, in a nutshell does the following:


1. When a column is used, check to see if it's rolled up. 

2. If it is rolled up, AND not used inside of an aggregate function, throw an error. If it's used inside of an aggregate function, check to see if this aggregation is actually valid for the rolled up column. This is done by checking with the Underlying Table associated with the column. For sketches, this means that sketches can only be used inside of a COUNT(DISTINCT ...) aggregate function.

Two additional mock tables were created to test this functionality inside the validator itself.   


## Complex Metrics
Another Druid concept called [complex metric types](http://druid.io/docs/latest/querying/segmentmetadataquery.html) have been introduced into the Druid adapter. Model definitions can now declare an alias for complex metrics so that may be used in SQL. Examples of this are in the **foodmart** and **wiki** model definitions. This helps hide the concept of sketches away from users, but also allows calcite to execute certain functions (e.g count distinct) more efficiently. 

The alias of a complex metric can also be the name of a dimension inside the model definition (see foodmart), and in this case calcite can use that dimension as normal, but will use the underlying complex metric to compute certain functions more efficiently.


## Additional Post Aggregation Support
After [CALCITE-1803](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CALCITE-1803) was merged, additional support for post aggregations was added so that results from sketch operations can be referenced inside the "postAggregations" field.


## VM
The druid VM ingestion files were also modified so that the **thetaSketch** complex metric type can be tested.

title: [CALCITE-1581] UDTF like in hive
body:
Hi, @julianhyde i have solved the issue [UDTF like in hive CALCITE-1581](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CALCITE-1581) with some tests.
 My solution is fairly straightforward, just translate the Hive `UDTF` grammar to the `CROSS JOIN LATERAL TABLE`, eg:
`
select udtf(empid) as (a1, a2) from emp;
equal to
SELECT t.a1, t.a2 from emps CROSS JOIN LATERAL TABLE(udf(empid)) as  t(s0, s1)
`

So, i modify the Parser.jj to implement above translation. And add `setHiveCompatible` to enable or  disable this feature. Tests case is under `SqlParserTest.java`, test function is `testHiveLikeUDTF`.
If you have time to review the my code, I will be very grateful.
Thanks, Sihua zhou.

[Jira ticket 1842](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CALCITE-1842) addressed the problem already:

The mistake in the input computation of `Sort` will make the LIMIT does not get pushed into the Druid Query. The difference in performance can be huge.
Right now this problem was reported only in Druid Adapter but this change is generic for all adapters, so specific Druid test cases were not created.

I did not find any test cases to check the cost of `RelNode` and do not know where to put the test cases if we want to test it out. If test cases are still necessary please let me know where to add.
